Body: Description: We have several servers that get scanned successfully for permissions but the data does not update in the Access Information Center.
Invitation updated. Attendees: No attendees listed
Invitation updated. Attendees: Frantz Baptiste, Stephen Byrd

As the executive sponsor for Extron, I was contacted by the client team on this ticket.

Met with the team 4/15/25.

NEA / AA version: 11.6.0.139

 

  • Scans have been erroring but completing a partial scan since 3/15/25. Appeared that scans using applet mode were not ending 'cleanly'
  • Verified all ports from app to proxy.
  • Cross checked T2 dates in FSAA for the server on proxy and application server and they all match.
  • Bulk import is functioning as expected.
  • Were able to see activity data tied to existing struc to current date and permission change data to 4/2/25.

 

Root Issue: Timestamp is not updating in AIC within the summary view. This creates uncertainty in data validity when producing reports

 

Troubleshooting taken

Restarted the proxy and kicked off scans again.

Directed user to permission change HTML 5 reports, removed the 100k row cap and made the report exportable

 

Client Feedback:

Scan completed 'cleanly' / success on this server via the proxy

Bulk import is now showing a T2 / T1 mismatch

 

I would like to request that we schedule a session with client to resolve T1 mismatch pls.

 

@Frantz Baptiste​  / @Eric Szymanski​  / @Brandon West​

@Frantz Baptiste​ On a call today for ticket 00442548 we found that from the NAA server, to the failed proxy servers port 8766 was not responding.

We validated that the firewall was disabled and that no network devices in between should be causing issues. We then rebooted the proxy server and port 8766 immediately started working again. The customer indicated that this issue happens daily and so I provided the following troubleshooting steps as I suspect the proxy service isn't responding, or the port bindings are somehow failing so restarting the proxy server service should start communication again. I don't think this will fix the customer problem, but it should point us to where the issue is coming from.

 

1. On the proxy server run netstat -aof | findstr :8766 and let us know what the output is.

2. On the NAA server, run tnc -computername <proxyserverIP> -port 8766 and provide the output.

3. Restart the proxy service on the proxy server.

4. Repeat steps 1 and 2.
Next Steps Updated: The root cause of information discrepancies in AIC is rooted in the failed bulk import being worked on 442548 and this ticket is being closed.
What We've Learned Updated: When logging in to the Access Information Center, the customer notices discrepancies in the data, as though the data has not been updated.
